---
title: Spicy Gochujang-Glazed Chicken with Horseradish Mashed Potatoes & Roasted Green Beans
description: Every element of this meal is punched up with flavor. You’ll cook chicken to sticky, tangy, sweet ‘n’ spicy perfection with a glaze made with gochujang sauce, ponzu, and sweet Thai chili sauce. Plus, you’ll infuse buttery mashed potatoes with horseradish for a little kick. Serve alongside green beans roasted with soy sauce for a dinner that brings delight to every bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65f0bcf7f15f35246a8cb54d-8c9d778e.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65f0bcf7f15f35246a8cb54d.pdf
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spicy-gochujang-glazed-chicken-65f0bcf7f15f35246a8cb54d
time required: 35 minutes
author: HelloFresh
cuisine: East Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 26 g
  saturated fat: 12 g
  carbohydrates: 49 g
  sugar: 14 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 5 g
  sodium: 1740 mg
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Dice @potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch pieces. Trim @green beans{6%ounce} if necessary.

Place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Reserve ½ cup potato cooking liquid, then drain. Return potatoes to #pot{} and cover to keep warm.

While potatoes cook, toss green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of oil, @soy sauce{2%tablespoon}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until browned and tender, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> Feel free to use less soy sauce if you prefer less saltiness!

Meanwhile, pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season all over with half the @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> If chicken begins to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium and cover pan with a lid.

Turn off heat; transfer chicken to a #plate{} to rest. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

Return same pan to stovetop over medium-low heat. Add @ponzu sauce{12%milliliters}, @gochujang sauce{½%ounce}, @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, and ¼ cup water; cook, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}.

Remove from heat and stir in @butter{1%tablespoon} until melted. Add cooked chicken to sauce and turn to coat.

> Use 2 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

To pot with potatoes, add @spicy horseradish paste{1%teaspoon}, remaining garlic powder, ¼ cup reserved potato cooking liquid, and @butter{2%tablespoon}. Mash until smooth with a #potato masher{}, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Taste and season with salt and pepper.

> Use ½ cup potato cooking liquid and 4 TBSP butter for 4 servings.

Divide chicken, green beans, and mashed potatoes between plates. Drizzle remaining sauce from pan over chicken. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.